POLOKWANE – South African National Equestrian Schools Association (Sanesa) riders from schools in the city recently participated in the first Limpopo qualifier for South Africa Western Mounted Games (SAWMGA). Riders and their horses gathered at Winnfield Stables on February 10 for the fun to start and not even the rain could prevent them from joining in the games. Read more in this week’s Polokwane Observer. Individual results:
Primary Schools:

